snippet: A teary-eyed Dana Barks was almost speechless after officials for the San Francisco's iconic Golden Gate Bridge approved a $76 million funding package for a suicide barrier that could prevent people from jumping to their deaths....

headline.print_headline: Tears, Joy at Vote to Fund Bridge Suicide Barrier
headline.main: Tears, Joy at Vote to Fund Bridge Suicide Barrier

lead_paragraph: A teary-eyed Dana Barks was almost speechless after officials for the San Francisco's iconic Golden Gate Bridge approved a $76 million funding package for a suicide barrier that could prevent people from jumping to their deaths.
